# AG-17098 — content staged by external/ag-shared/scripts/rulesync-fetch/.
# Patterns cover everything delivered via ag-dev-prompts plugins; local-only
# items (skills, commands, rules) remain tracked via allowlist entries.

.fetched-from-ag-dev-prompts
mcp.json

# Plugin-delivered skills — allowlist local-only skills
/skills/*
!/skills/technology-stack/
!/skills/docs-e2e-tests/

# Plugin-delivered agents — all agents live in plugins
/subagents/*.md

# Plugin-delivered commands — allowlist local-only ag-grid dev loops.
# docs-review and release-docs-review are delivered as skills by
# ag-prodeng; invoke as /ag-prodeng:docs-review etc. (auto-detects ag-grid
# via packages/ag-grid-community/src).
/commands/*.md
/commands/docs/
!/commands/docs-e2e-tests.md
!/commands/manual-test.md

# Plugin-delivered rules — allowlist local-only rules (ag-grid-specific).
# The ag-grid flavours of benchmarks/docs-pages/examples/testing share filenames
# with ag-charts plugin guides; the ag-grid checkout relies on stage.py's
# product filter (ag-grid/ag-shared#5) to stop staging ag-charts guides here,
# so these tracked files are not overwritten.
/rules/*.md
!/rules/ag-grid.md
!/rules/benchmarks.md
!/rules/docs-example-specs.md
!/rules/docs-pages.md
!/rules/examples.md
!/rules/framework-view-layers.md
!/rules/testing.md
# docs-review-testing.md ships as a sibling asset of the ag-prodeng docs-review
# skill config (at skills/docs-review/ag-grid/), not as a top-level rule, so no
# allowlist entry is needed here.
